 Middelburg Primary School have erected a “Slow down, Frogs Crossing” sign in Mandela Drive, urging motorists to avoid killing African bullfrogs.      The Eco Monitors said that it was with great concern that they noticed the large number of frogs that were killed after the rains on the evening of Friday, 21 October. Read: Start your day by eating a live frog  They approached the Traffic Department who willingly assisted in the erection of the signs. Read: The Kamasutra, froggy style Read: MPS has brain power Read: Verwoerd’s assassin went to MPS